# ─── REQUIRED: Backend URL (for the watch page to function) ───
# On Vercel: you can leave this EMPTY — the app auto-detects VERCEL_URL.
# On local dev: defaults to http://localhost:3000/api (same-origin proxy).
# Override only if you want to point to a different backend.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=""

# ─── OPTIONAL: Consumet API instance (for real anime streaming) ───
# Self-host Consumet: https://github.com/consumet/api.consumet.org
# ⚠️ The public api.consumet.org endpoint is DEAD (HTTP 451). Must self-host.
# CONSUMET_URL="https://your-consumet-instance.com"

# ─── OPTIONAL: Cloudflare Worker URL (offloads stream bandwidth from Vercel) ───
# Deploy the Worker in ./cf-worker (see cf-worker/README.md for full instructions).
#
# The Worker does TWO jobs (both free, no card, no external service):
#   1. Stream proxy — adds Referer/Origin headers to video CDN requests
#      (saves your 10GB/mo Vercel bandwidth quota)
#   2. AllAnime episode resolver — solves Turnstile captcha via Cloudflare
#      Browser Rendering (free 10 min/day of browser CPU, no external solver)
#
# Deploy steps (5 min, no card):
#   1. npm install -g wrangler
#   2. wrangler login   (opens browser, click "Allow" — no card needed)
#   3. cd cf-worker
#   4. npm install   (installs @cloudflare/puppeteer)
#   5. wrangler deploy
#   6. Copy the resulting https://xan-stream-proxy.<subdomain>.workers.dev URL
#   7. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_CF_WORKER_URL to that URL in Vercel env vars
#   8. Redeploy Vercel
#
# Cost: $0/month (Cloudflare Workers free tier + Browser Rendering free tier)
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CF_WORKER_URL="https://xan-stream-proxy.your-subdomain.workers.dev"

# ─── ALTERNATIVE: Free Solver VPS (if you can't use Cloudflare Workers) ───
# If for some reason you can't use Cloudflare Workers, the free solver runs
# Puppeteer on a free VPS or your local computer. See free-solver/README.md.
#
# Two no-card paths:
#   Path A — Local + Cloudflare Quick Tunnel (zero signup, zero card)
#     cd free-solver && ./start-with-tunnel.sh
#   Path B — Render.com free tier (GitHub signup only, no card)
#
# If you set NEXT_PUBLIC_FREE_SOLVER_URL, it takes precedence over
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CF_WORKER_URL for episode source resolution.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FREE_SOLVER_URL="https://your-solver-url"
# SOLVER_SECRET="some-random-string"  # optional shared secret for security




